# Target Numbers and Difficulty

Every time you attempt an action with uncertain outcome, you roll 2d6 and add relevant modifiers. The total must meet or exceed a target number (TN) to succeed. Choosing appropriate target numbers is one of the most important GM skills—set them too low and success becomes trivial, too high and failure becomes inevitable.

Autumn Phoenix RPG uses a standardized TN scale that remains consistent throughout the game. Unlike systems where DCs scale with level, these target numbers represent absolute difficulty. A TN 8 task is equally challenging for beginning characters and legendary heroes—the difference is that heroes have higher bonuses and succeed more reliably.

